---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Badmouth Digital" description="If we disappeared tomorrow, every system we've built would still be running. That's the point." currentPage="about">

    <!-- SECTION 1 — THE TEST -->
    <section class="section section--hero surface-base noise-bg has-scanlines" style="position: relative; min-height: auto; padding-top: var(--space-24); padding-bottom: var(--space-12);">
        <div class="grid-page">
            <div class="col-content stack-4 text-center">
                <div style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; margin-inline: auto;">
                    <span class="status-dot status-dot--live"></span>
                    <p class="t-eyebrow" style="margin: 0;">About Badmouth</p>
                </div>
                <h1 class="t-display t-display--hero" style="margin-inline: auto;">
                    IF WE DISAPPEARED<br />
                    TOMORROW, YOUR SYSTEM<br />
                    <span style="color: var(--color-brand);">WOULD STILL BE RUNNING.</span>
                </h1>
                <p class="t-body t-body--lg" style="margin-inline: auto; max-width: 55ch; color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600;">
                    That's the test. That's the whole point. We build systems that don't need us to keep working.
                </p>
                <p class="t-body t-body--md" style="margin-inline: auto; max-width: 55ch;">
                    Most agencies build dependency. They hold your accounts. They own your data. They keep doing work that only works while they're doing it. If you leave, everything stops.
                </p>
                <p class="t-body t-body--md" style="margin-inline: auto; max-width: 55ch; color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600;">
                    We build the opposite. You own everything. It runs without us. We stay because you want us to — not because you have to.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 2 — WHY WE EXIST -->
    <section class="section section--padded surface-sunken">
        <div class="grid-page grid-align-center grid-gap-lg">
            <div class="col-left-7 stack-4">
                <p class="t-eyebrow">Why We Exist</p>
                <h2 class="t-display t-display--section">
                    WE GOT TIRED OF<br />
                    <span class="t-accent t-crt-shake">WATCHING GOOD BUSINESSES</span><br />
                    <span style="color: var(--color-brand);">GET SCREWED BY BAD MARKETING.</span>
                </h2>
                <p class="t-body t-body--md" style="max-width: 55ch;">
                    A guy who's been fixing furnaces for 20 years shouldn't need an MBA to figure out why his marketing doesn't work. He shouldn't be paying $2,000/month to an agency that sends him a PDF full of graphs once a month.
                </p>
                <p class="t-body t-body--md" style="max-width: 55ch;">
                    He needs a system that catches leads, follows up, and tells him where his money's going. That's it. That's the whole gap.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-right-5">
                <div class="retro-box" style="padding: var(--space-6);">
                    <p class="t-body" style="color: var(--color-brand); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 0.7rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">What we believe</p>
                    <div class="stack-3">
                        <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-brand); padding-left: var(--space-3);">
                            <p class="t-body t-body--sm" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600;">Systems first. Volume second.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--theme-accent-teal); padding-left: var(--space-3);">
                            <p class="t-body t-body--sm" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600;">You should own everything.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--theme-accent-yellow); padding-left: var(--space-3);">
                            <p class="t-body t-body--sm" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600;">If it doesn't run without us, we failed.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-brand); padding-left: var(--space-3);">
                            <p class="t-body t-body--sm" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600;">Real businesses deserve real systems.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 3 — PHILOSOPHY -->
    <section class="section section--statement section--padded surface-base">
        <div class="grid-page">
            <div class="col-content stack-6 text-center">
                <h2 class="t-display t-display--section" style="margin-inline: auto;">
                    BUILD THE SYSTEM FIRST.<br />
                    <span class="t-accent t-flicker">THEN TURN UP THE VOLUME.</span>
                </h2>
                <p class="t-body t-body--lg" style="margin-inline: auto; max-width: 55ch;">
                    Most marketing agencies start at Layer 3. Run ads. Drive traffic. Hope it converts. And when it doesn't? They blame the market, not the system.
                </p>
                <p class="t-body t-body--md" style="margin-inline: auto; max-width: 55ch;">
                    We start at Layer 1. Build the foundation. Make sure every lead gets caught, followed up, tracked, and measured. Then add SEO. Then ads. In order.
                </p>
                <p class="t-body t-body--md" style="margin-inline: auto; max-width: 55ch; color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600;">
                    It's not sexy. It's not fast. But it works. And it keeps working.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4 — WHAT MAKES US DIFFERENT -->
    <section class="section section--padded surface-elevated">
        <div class="grid-page grid-gap-lg">
            <div class="col-full text-center stack-4">
                <p class="t-eyebrow">What Makes Us Different</p>
                <h2 class="t-display t-display--section" style="margin-inline: auto;">
                    THREE THINGS NOBODY ELSE<br />
                    <span class="t-accent t-flicker">IS DOING.</span>
                </h2>
            </div>
            <div class="col-full">
                <div class="inner-grid-3">
                    <div class="card stack-3" style="border-top: 3px solid var(--color-brand);">
                        <h3 class="t-display t-display--card">WHAT HAPPENS AFTER</h3>
                        <p class="t-body t-body--sm">
                            Most agencies focus on driving traffic. We focus on what happens when it shows up. The capture. The follow-up. The tracking. The conversion. That's where the money is.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card stack-3" style="border-top: 3px solid var(--theme-accent-teal);">
                        <h3 class="t-display t-display--card">JOBS, NOT CLICKS</h3>
                        <p class="t-body t-body--sm">
                            We don't report on impressions. We track leads, response times, source attribution, and revenue. If you can't tie it to a job, it doesn't mean anything.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card stack-3" style="border-top: 3px solid var(--theme-accent-yellow);">
                        <h3 class="t-display t-display--card">CONTINUOUS VS. CAMPAIGN</h3>
                        <p class="t-body t-body--sm">
                            Campaigns stop when the budget runs out. Systems don't. Review requests fire after every job. Follow-ups run on every lead. Your system works 24/7, 365.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 5 — WHO WE WORK WITH -->
    <section class="section section--padded surface-base">
        <div class="grid-page grid-align-center grid-gap-lg">
            <div class="col-left-7 stack-4">
                <p class="t-eyebrow">Who We Work With</p>
                <h2 class="t-display t-display--section">
                    LOCAL SERVICE BUSINESSES<br />
                    <span class="t-accent t-flicker">WHO ALREADY HAVE DEMAND.</span>
                </h2>
                <p class="t-body t-body--md" style="max-width: 55ch;">
                    HVAC. Plumbing. Electrical. Roofing. Landscaping. Garage doors. Pest control. Concrete. Cleaning. If you answer calls, drive trucks, and fix things — you're who we built this for.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-right-5">
                <div class="card stack-3" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-text-muted);">
                    <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">NOT A FIT IF:</p>
                    <p class="t-body t-body--sm" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">✗ You're a startup still finding product-market fit</p>
                    <p class="t-body t-body--sm" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">✗ You need brand awareness before leads</p>
                    <p class="t-body t-body--sm" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">✗ You want someone to "just run ads"</p>
                    <p class="t-body t-body--sm" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">✗ You're looking for the cheapest option</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section section--cta section--padded section--mic-drop has-scanlines" style="position: relative;">
        <div class="grid-page" style="position: relative; z-index: 2;">
            <div class="col-content text-center stack-4">
                <h2 class="t-display t-display--section" style="color: #fff; margin-inline: auto;">
                    DONE DUCT-TAPING<br />
                    <span class="mic-drop__headline">IT TOGETHER?</span>
                </h2>
                <p class="t-body t-body--lg" style="margin-inline: auto; max-width: 50ch; margin-top: var(--space-4);">
                    Tell us what's going on. We'll tell you what to fix first.
                </p>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: var(--space-4); justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: var(--space-4);">
                    <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--lg">Install Your System →</a>
                    <a href="/see-the-system" class="btn btn--lg btn--mic-outline">See The System</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- REINFORCEMENT -->
    <section class="section section--statement section--padded-sm surface-pure">
        <div class="grid-page">
            <div class="col-content text-center">
                <p class="t-body t-body--lg" style="margin-inline: auto; max-width: 55ch; color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                    If we disappeared tomorrow, your system would still be running. <span style="color: var(--color-brand); font-weight: 700;">That's the whole point.</span>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

</BaseLayout>
